---
title: Miso Ramen
servings: 2
tags:
  - japanese
  - ramen
  - soup
---

= Tare (Seasoning Base)

In a #small bowl{}, combine @white miso paste{3%tbsp}, @soy sauce{1%tbsp},
@mirin{1%tbsp}, and @sesame paste{1%tbsp}(tahini works too).

= Broth

In a #large pot{}, heat @sesame oil{1%tbsp} over medium heat. Sauté
@garlic{3%cloves}(minced), @ginger{1%tbsp}(grated), and @scallion whites{2}(chopped)
for ~{2%minutes}.

Add @ground pork{4%oz} and cook for ~{3%minutes} until browned.

Add @chicken stock{4%cups} and @dashi stock{1%cup}. Bring to a simmer for ~{10%minutes}.

Stir in the tare. Keep warm but do not boil.

-- Boiling miso kills the probiotics and dulls the flavor.

= Toppings

Soft-boil @eggs{2} for ~soft boil{6.5%minutes}. Ice bath, peel, halve.

Slice @chashu pork{4%slices} or pan-sear @pork belly{6%oz}(sliced).

= Assemble

Cook @fresh ramen noodles{2%portions} in boiling water for ~{90%seconds}. Drain.

Divide noodles between bowls. Ladle broth over. Top with egg halves,
chashu, @corn kernels{1/4%cup}, @nori{2%sheets}, @scallion greens{2}(sliced),
and @chili oil{} to taste.
